        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 6:38PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 638 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Ball Ground, or 8 miles
south of Jasper, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Canton, Jasper, Ball Ground, Nelson, Waleska, Buffington, Salacoa
Valley, Lake Tamarack, Hollis Lathem Reservoir, Marblehill, Tate, and
Reavis Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
